### Meaning of buy---->>

Again,
buy = 1
means
I DON'T own a stock.
I CAN buy.

buy = 0
means
I already own a stock.
I CAN'T buy.
I can sell.


Observe carefully.

While computing row i, we only use

i + 1

We never use

i + 2
i + 3

So we only need the next row.

Let's call it ahead and the current row curr

ALSO--> 

So DP becomes dp[i][buy]

Size?

n + 1 rows
2 columns

Why n+1?

Because we have the base case  i == n
When we've processed all days: i == n

There are no more days left to trade. So the profit is 0

So
vector<vector<int>> dp(n + 1, vector<int>(2, 0));

Notice we initialize with 0 because

dp[n][0] = 0
dp[n][1] = 0

is our base case.

CODE- SPACE OPTIMIZED 

class Solution {
public:
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {

        int n = prices.size();

        vector<int> ahead(2, 0), curr(2, 0);

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {

            curr[1] = max(-prices[i] + ahead[0], ahead[1]);

            curr[0] = max(prices[i] + ahead[1],ahead[0]);

            ahead = curr;
        }

        return ahead[1];
    }
};

